If launch crashes with "Invalid camera_pair 'left'":
  the robot still has the old physical_four_camera_node.py installed
  copy physical_four_camera_node.py to the robot, rebuild gr4_camera_config, and source install/setup.bash again

Trolley-ready approach:
  trolley_stage_offset_y is now 0.9 instead of 1.0 for a slightly stricter approach pose
  if Nav2 still stops too loosely, tune the robot Nav2 goal_checker xy/yaw tolerances

If drive_under is blocked by Nav2/lidar/twist mux, launch explicitly with:
ros2 launch gr4_camera_config physical_staged_trolley_mission.launch.py \
  enable_motion:=true \
  straight_under_distance_m:=1.30 \
  straight_under_speed:=0.07 \
  straight_under_x_hold_kp:=0.30 \
  straight_under_max_vx_correction:=0.025 \
  drive_under_extra_cmd_vel_topic:=/cmd_vel_joy \
  drive_under_lidar_ignore_radius:=1.25 \
  drive_under_stop_on_under_markers:=true \
  drive_under_marker_stop_min_progress:=0.20 \
  drive_under_marker_stop_hold_sec:=0.0 \
  fine_acquire_enable:=true \
  fine_acquire_front_seen_vx:=0.012 \
  fine_reacquire_after_pair_loss:=true \
  fine_position_tolerance_x:=0.025 \
  fine_position_tolerance_y:=0.010 \
  side_require_target_pair_visible:=false

If fine_align sees visible=[] under the trolley, drive_under did not go far enough:
  drive_under now uses front/rear cameras and stops early once enough underside ArUcos are visible
  straight_under_distance_m default is now 1.30 as a maximum distance
  if it is still short, relaunch with straight_under_distance_m:=1.35
  if it goes too far, relaunch with straight_under_distance_m:=1.25
  tune early stop with drive_under_marker_stop_min_progress:=0.20 and drive_under_marker_stop_hold_sec:=0.0

Fine-align debugging:
  the controller now logs and publishes fine_debug once per second on /physical_docking_status
  it includes front/rear/left/right ArUco IDs, active pair, target, error, and cmd_vel
ros2 topic echo /physical_docking_status

If fine_align detects only front underside ArUcos and no rear ArUcos:
  it now creeps toward robot front with fine_acquire_front_seen_vx:=0.012
  if that is the wrong direction, relaunch with fine_acquire_front_seen_vx:=-0.012

Fine alignment can run with one front and one rear underside ArUco:
  min_under_markers default is now 2, with front=1 and rear=1 still required
  fine align now chooses one sane front/rear marker pair instead of averaging every flickering marker
  sparse fine-align pairs must use opposite trolley local-y rows, e.g. 12+3 or 10+5, not same-row pairs like 10+3
  fine_estimate_window_size default is 3 so it does not wait too long for sparse markers
  fine yaw tolerance default is now 12 deg so it prioritizes x/y centering
  fine_reacquire_after_pair_loss default is true so if rear/front markers disappear after a pair was seen, it can creep to recover them

Calibration note:
  trolley_reference_summary_20260603_200123.csv is a flipped_180 centered pose
  all four markers estimate target_offset_x=0.1378 target_offset_y=0.0037
  staged defaults use target_offset_x=0.1378 target_offset_y=0.0038
  the successful hand-assisted fine-align also ended at target_offset_x=0.1378 target_offset_y=0.0038
  fine_align now keeps x tolerance at 0.025m but tightens y tolerance to 0.010m
  optional separate normal/flipped offsets exist:
  use_orientation_target_offsets:=true
  target_offset_x_normal:=... target_offset_y_normal:=...
  target_offset_x_flipped:=0.1378 target_offset_y_flipped:=0.0038

